<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_78af8a14-05bf-40b2-a42c-197be6dc47eb" outputclass="ncc-clause" variation="SA"><sptc>G7D2</sptc><title id="_1bb1afa1-c26f-4dce-b5a9-c5d60fcef21a">Livable housing design</title><subclause id="_d0d7e274-bd05-4d6a-97c3-793feb96f640" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_5b6cf36d-508a-4759-8b5e-23677b07ce83">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>Each <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1473_0.4.0.xml#_d2c89488-8a36-464b-94f6-a91d0f5a6c9c" id="_4d33b9b4-b8f7-4a63-9d00-856354b9fa02" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">sole-occupancy unit</xref> in a Class 2 building must comply with the ABCB Standard for Livable Housing Design, except for Part 1.</p></subclause><subclause id="_2b856b80-2eb0-4bbc-bf1f-0147ef57f23a" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_00708491-9de2-44d9-b873-584055e5a485">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p>The <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1445_0.13.0.xml#_b30a308f-eb9f-4549-a6c1-19d5f32a5272" id="_cf3cbe2f-d9c7-4323-84ce-71789aa39da2" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">sanitary compartment</xref> that is subject to Clause 4.1 of the ABCB Standard for Livable Housing Design may be located on either:</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_4e3e48a5-3f39-409c-8c16-2c1b735fdcda">the ground or entry level; or</li><li id="_a99bd331-1126-47b7-b3b0-5bcd408393bd">the lowest level containing a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1326_0.4.0.xml#_b8eec66f-9c05-425d-8474-e6a2dfc2c0f4" id="_fc4fa928-ac1f-40c8-847c-12145e88d532" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">habitable room</xref> within the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1473_0.4.0.xml#_d2c89488-8a36-464b-94f6-a91d0f5a6c9c" id="_37f2fa14-5072-4086-86ee-d1256a4d4ffc" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">sole-occupancy unit</xref> of a Class 2 building.</li></ol></subclause><callout id="_b77e0e2f-877e-410d-950d-28d7181597ff"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><p>Part 1 of the <xref format="html" href="https://abcb.gov.au/sites/default/files/resources/2023/livable-housing-design-20230406.pdf" id="_eb683e5c-9891-47c0-a643-18670d358408" scope="external">ABCB Standard for Livable Housing Design</xref> requires a step-free access path from a parking space or property boundary, to the dwelling entry door. For Class 2 buildings, this requirement is already addressed by <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/26_0.10.0.xml#_0422da33-ebd2-4d7c-994c-31d8dad5aa0f" id="_6397bd89-4b9a-4751-a9e1-2be8f394354e" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-part">Part D4</xref> and the Disability (Access to Premises—Buildings) Standards 2010. Therefore, it is not necessary to apply Part 1 of the ABCB Standard for Livable Housing Design to a Class 2 building.</p></callout></clause>